            <h2 id="order-matters">Getting the Order Right</h2>
            <p>The most common mistake when merging PDFs is getting the page order wrong. Here's a systematic approach:</p>

            <div class="article-checklist">
                <div class="article-check"><span>1</span><div><strong>Plan your structure before uploading</strong><p>Write out the intended order of documents before you start. For complex merges with 10+ files, a simple numbered list helps avoid mistakes.</p></div></div>
                <div class="article-check"><span>2</span><div><strong>Name your files numerically</strong><p>Rename files to 01_Cover.pdf, 02_Summary.pdf, 03_Appendix.pdf before uploading. Many merge tools auto-sort by filename.</p></div></div>
                <div class="article-check"><span>3</span><div><strong>Use the drag-to-reorder feature</strong><p>PdfToolStack's merge tool lets you drag and drop files into any order after uploading, so you don't have to get it perfect on the first try.</p></div></div>
                <div class="article-check"><span>4</span><div><strong>Preview before downloading</strong><p>If the tool offers a preview, check the first and last few pages of the merged document to confirm the order is correct.</p></div></div>
            </div>

            <h2 id="page-ranges">Merging Specific Pages Only</h2>
            <p>Sometimes you don't want the entire document — just certain pages. For example, you might want pages 1–3 from one PDF and pages 5–8 from another.</p>
            <p>For this workflow:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Use PdfToolStack's <a href="/split-pdf">Split PDF tool</a> to extract the specific pages you need from each document</li>
                <li>Download the extracted page ranges as separate PDFs</li>
                <li>Upload those extracted PDFs to the <a href="/merge-pdf">Merge PDF tool</a> and combine them in order</li>
            </ol>
            <p>This two-step approach gives you precise control over exactly which pages end up in the final document.</p>

